# COBOL Item Ledger Strategy Example
# Controls execution priority scales and limits for sequential record I/O loops.

DATA DIVISION.
01 ITEM-ID      PIC 9 USAGE R0.
01 ITEM-BALANCE PIC 9 USAGE R1.
01 THRESHOLD    PIC 9 USAGE R2.

PROCEDURE DIVISION.
    MOVE 100 TO ITEM-BALANCE.
    MOVE 50 TO THRESHOLD.
    
    IF ITEM-BALANCE > THRESHOLD
        SET depth 5.
    ELSE
        SET depth 2.
    END-IF.
    
    # Evaluate priority adjustments
    EVAL.
